# .windsurfrules — Windsurf Cascade project rules
# Entry point: read AGENTS.md first, then follow the Vibe Layer Map.

## Key project rules (from LAYER-1/rules.md)

1. **6 fixed statuses** — New, To Read, Important, Archive, Verified, Outdated.
   No additions, no renaming. Archive and Outdated are terminal.
2. **Single-user allowlist** — every handler checks `from_user.id == TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USER_ID`.
   Unauthorized users receive no data and no acknowledgment.
3. **Dynamic topic tree** — topics are dynamic (no enums, no hardcoded IDs).
   Hierarchy is cycle-free (ltree containment). Renames cascade to descendants.
4. **Migrations are mandatory** — any DB schema change requires an Alembic migration
   tested on a clean database. Seed data must be present after `alembic upgrade head`.
5. **Secrets only in .env** — bot token, user ID, DB credentials live in `.env` only.
   `.env` is never committed to git.
6. **Git workflow via branches and PR** — follow `GIT_WORKFLOW.md`. Never commit
   directly to `main`. Feature work in `feature/…`, fixes in `fix/…`, docs in `docs/…`.

## Quick references

- `AGENTS.md` — AI workspace entry point and layer map
- `LAYER-1/rules.md` — full invariants
